StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: DESCRIBE variable;


The DESCRIBE statement is used to display the data type of a variable. 

The following example stores the result of the serverStatus action in the variable that is named r. 
The DESCRIBE statement shows that the result is a list that includes three entries: 

 o About (which is itself a list as well)
 o server (a table)
 o nodestatus (also a table)

Example:
  action serverstatus result=r submit; 
  run;

  describe r;
  run;

Syntax: [CALL] function( arg1, arg2,...);

Calls function with the specified arguments. If the function returns a value, it is ignored. 
The call keyword is optional.

StatementOptionHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: DO UNTIL (condition); statements; END;

This is a traditional do until loop. Loop until the condition is false where the check is at the end 
of the loop.

Syntax: DO [<key>,] <var> OVER <value>; statements; END; 

Iterate over a list. The key or index for the list can be placed into <key>. The variable contexts accessed as <var> and the list is referenced as <value>. 

The variable is not a copy by the value itself.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: FUNCITON name( [argument_spec [, argument_spec ...]] );statements; END func;

This create a new function that can be called in an expression. This will replace an existing function 
of the same name. The default return value will be zero unless the return statement is specified.

