StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: SESSION session-name; 
Syntax: SESSION (“session-name”);  

Specifies an existing session to use for running a program. 

Required Argument:
session-name
  specifies the name of an existing session.

Syntax: WHEN (when-expressions) statement; 

If any of the expressions are true, execute the statement. 

Usage:
select [(select-expression)]; 
when (when-expressions) statement; 
otherwise statement; end [select];

The first WHEN statement to match the expression will have its statements executed.

Syntax: OTHERWISE statement; 

Usage:
select [(select-expression)]; 
when (when-expressions) statement; 
otherwise statement; end [select];

If no statements match and an OTHERWISE statement is specified, then it is executed.

Syntax: SOURCE <variable>; <text>; <text>; ENDSOURCE; 

The source statement allows you to embed text in the program and assign it to the given variable. 
After this statement executes, the variable has the string value of the text. This is useful when 
a user wants to embed graph commands that can be sent to a graph function. For example: 

 import graphlib;
 source instruction;
 plot x/y;
 spline;
 endsource;

 rc = graphplot( instruction );
